Fix the themed-scrollbar geometry inflation on Eclipse 2026-03+ (4.39/4.40)
at display scales other than 100%.

SWT 3.133 replaced Control.autoScaleDisabled (a boolean whose default was
correct even when constructors are skipped) with the AutoscalingMode enum,
initialized to ENABLED by a field initializer. DevStyle creates its scrollbar
adapters via sun.misc.Unsafe.allocateInstance, which skips field
initializers, so the adapter's mode is null and SWT treats it as
"autoscaling disabled": bounds are written at the parent's zoom but read
back at 100, inflating adapted popup scrollables by the display scale factor
(1.5x at 150%). Dialogs like Debug Configurations get their bottom cut off
and the scrollbar cannot reach the last items (upstream report:
github.com/CodeTogether-Inc/CodeTogether issue #444). Copy autoscalingMode
from the source widget before createWidget; a no-op on pre-2026-03 SWT.

Target: com.genuitec.eclipse.theming.scrollbar 2025.2.0.202509301431
Context source: the bundle jar's embedded sources (src/**, codeaffine
FlatScrollBar, EPL-1.0). Details: docs/scrollbar-autoscaling.md

--- a/com.genuitec.eclipse.theming.scrollbar/src/com/codeaffine/eclipse/swt/widget/scrollable/ScrollableAdapterFactory.java
+++ b/com.genuitec.eclipse.theming.scrollbar/src/com/codeaffine/eclipse/swt/widget/scrollable/ScrollableAdapterFactory.java
@@ -22,6 +22,7 @@
 import static java.util.Arrays.asList;
 import static java.util.Collections.unmodifiableList;
 
+import java.lang.reflect.Field;
 import java.util.ArrayList;
 import java.util.Collection;
 import java.util.List;
@@ -147,11 +148,24 @@
         Integer zoom = reflectionUtil.getField( scrollable, ZOOM, Integer.class );
         reflectionUtil.setField( result, ZOOM, zoom );
       } catch (Throwable bestEffort) {}
+      copyAutoscalingMode( scrollable, result );
       reflectionUtil.invoke( result, CREATE_WIDGET, $( valueOf( 0 ), int.class ) );
     }
     return result;
   }
 
+  // SWT 3.133+ (Eclipse 2026-03) initializes Control.autoscalingMode in a field
+  // initializer, which Unsafe.allocateInstance skips; a null mode makes the
+  // adapter read its bounds at zoom 100 while writing them at the parent's
+  // zoom, inflating adapted scrollables on displays scaled above 100%.
+  private static void copyAutoscalingMode( Scrollable scrollable, Scrollable result ) {
+    try {
+      Field mode = Control.class.getDeclaredField( "autoscalingMode" );
+      mode.setAccessible( true );
+      mode.set( result, mode.get( scrollable ) );
+    } catch (Throwable bestEffort) {}
+  }
+
   private static void applyDrawingOrderOrdinalNumber( Control control, int ordinalNumber ) {
     control.moveAbove( control.getParent().getChildren()[ ordinalNumber ] );
   }
